table= pd.DataFrame(columns=["Address","Price","Detail","Links"])
houses = soup9.find_all('div', class_ = 'list-card-info')
for house in houses:
    try:
        address = house.find('address', {'class':'list-card-addr' }).text
        price = house.find('div', {'class':'list-card-price' }).text.split("$")[1].replace(",","")
        detail = house.find('ul', {'class':'list-card-details' }).text
        link = house.a['href']
        
        
    except Exception as e:
        address=None
        price=None
        detail=None
        link=None
    
    table= table.append({"Address":address,"Price":price,"Detail":detail,"Links":link},
                    ignore_index=True)

for house in houses:
    try:
        address = house.find('address', {'class':'list-card-addr' }).text

        link = house.a['href']

        address=None
        price=None
        detail=None
        link=None

                    ignore_index=True)

df['beds'] = df['beds'].replace('<abbr class="list-card-label"> <!-- -->bds</abbr></li><li>', ' ', regex=True)
df['beds'] = df['beds'].replace('<abbr class="list-card-label"> <!-- -->ba</abbr></li><li>', ' ', regex=True)
df['beds'] = df['beds'].replace('<abbr class="list-card-label"> <!-- -->bd</abbr></li><li>', ' ', regex=True)
df['beds'] = df['beds'].replace('<abbr class="list-card-label"> <!-- -->sqft</abbr></li></ul>', ' ', regex=True)
df['beds'] = df['beds'].replace(' abbr></li><li class="">', '|', regex=True)
df['beds'] = df['beds'].replace('Studio</li><li>', '0 ', regex=True)
df['beds'] = df['beds'].replace('<abbr class="list-card-label"> <!-- -->ba</', ' ', regex=True)
df['beds'] = df['beds'].replace(' abbr></li><li class="">', '|', regex=True)
df['beds'] = df['beds'].replace('<abbr class="list-card-label"> <!-- -->sqft</abbr></li><li class="list-card-statusText">- House for sale</li></ul>', ' ', regex=True)
df['beds'] = df['beds'].replace('<abbr class="list-card-label"> <!-- -->sqft</abbr></li><li class="list-card-statusText">- Condo for sale</li></ul>', ' ', regex=True)
df['beds'] = df['beds'].replace('<abbr class="list-card-label"> <!-- -->sqft</abbr></li><li class="list-card-statusText">-<abbr class="list-card-label"> <!-- -->Active</abbr></li></ul>', ' ', regex=True)
df['beds'] = df['beds'].replace('<abbr class="list-card-label"> <!-- -->bd</abbr></li><li class="">', '|', regex=True)

table= pd.DataFrame(columns=["Address","Price","Detail","Links"])
houses = soup6.find_all('div', class_ = 'list-card-info')
for house in houses:
    try:
        address = house.find('address', {'class':'list-card-addr' }).text
        price = house.find('div', {'class':'list-card-price' }).text.split("$")[1].replace(",","")
        detail = house.find('ul', {'class':'list-card-details' }).text
        brokerage = house(soup.find_all(class_= 'list-card-brokerage list-card-img-overlay',text=True))
        link = house.a['href']
        
        
    except Exception as e:
        address=None
        price=None
        detail=None
        link=None
        brokerage=None
    
    table= table.append({"Address":address,"Price":price,"Detail":detail,"Links":link,"Brokerage":brokerage},
                    ignore_index=True)

            // Polyfill for IE11
            Math.tanh = Math.tanh || function(x){
                var a = Math.exp(+x), b = Math.exp(-x);
                return a == Infinity ? 1 : (b == Infinity ? -1 : (a - b) / (a + b));
            }

            function degreesToRadians(deg) {
              return deg * (Math.PI / 180);
            }

            function radiansToDegrees(rad) {
              return rad / (Math.PI / 180);
            }

            function getBoundsAndZoomLevel(northLat, southLat, westLng, eastLng, spaceHeight, spaceWidth) {
                var WORLD_DIM = { height: 256, width: 256 };
                var ZOOM_MAX = 19;

                function latRad(lat) {
                    var sin = Math.sin(degreesToRadians(lat));
                    var radX2 = Math.log((1 + sin) / (1 - sin)) / 2;
                    return Math.max(Math.min(radX2, Math.PI), -Math.PI) / 2;
                }

                function fracToZoom(mapPx, worldPx, fraction) {
                    var v = Math.log(mapPx / worldPx / fraction) / Math.LN2;
                    // Adjust for floating error on exact fit
                    return Math.floor(v + 0.00001);
                }

                function zoomToFrac(mapPx, worldPx, zoom) {
                    return (mapPx / worldPx) / Math.exp(zoom * Math.LN2);
                }

                // ====================================================================
                // Calculate the zoom level to fit these bounds into the given viewport
                // ====================================================================

                // Sphere math to turn lat and long into degrees out of 360
                var latRadNorth = latRad(northLat);
                var latRadSouth = latRad(southLat);
                var latRadDiff = latRadNorth - latRadSouth;
                var latFraction = latRadDiff / Math.PI;

                var lngDiff = eastLng - westLng;
                var lngFraction = ((!(lngDiff >= 0)) ? (lngDiff + 360) : lngDiff) / 360;

                var latZoom = fracToZoom(spaceHeight, WORLD_DIM.height, latFraction);
                var lngZoom = fracToZoom(spaceWidth, WORLD_DIM.width, lngFraction);

                var finalZoom = Math.min(latZoom, lngZoom, ZOOM_MAX);

                // ========================================================
                // Calculate the viewport-exact bounds for this zoom level
                // ========================================================

                var fittedLngFraction = zoomToFrac(spaceWidth, WORLD_DIM.width, finalZoom);
                var lngDegreeCenter = (eastLng + westLng) / 2;
                var fittedLngDiff = lngDiff * (fittedLngFraction / lngFraction)
                var fittedWestLng = lngDegreeCenter - (fittedLngDiff / 2);
                var fittedEastLng = lngDegreeCenter + (fittedLngDiff / 2);

                var fittedLatRadFraction = zoomToFrac(spaceHeight, WORLD_DIM.height, finalZoom);
                var latRadCenter = (latRadNorth + latRadSouth) / 2;
                var fittedLatRadDiff = latRadDiff * (fittedLatRadFraction / latFraction);
                var fittedNorthLat = radiansToDegrees(Math.asin(Math.tanh(2 * (latRadCenter + (fittedLatRadDiff/2)))));
                var fittedSouthLat = radiansToDegrees(Math.asin(Math.tanh(2 * (latRadCenter - (fittedLatRadDiff/2)))));

                return {
                    zoom: finalZoom,
                    bounds: {
                        northLat: fittedNorthLat,
                        southLat: fittedSouthLat,
                        eastLng: fittedEastLng,
                        westLng: fittedWestLng,
                    }
                }
            }

            /*
                This must be kept synchronized with these vars in https://gitlab.zgtools.net/zillow/searchxp/static-search-page/-/blob/master/src/search-app/less/constants.less
                    @wideSingleColumnMinWidth
                    @wideDoubleColumnMinWidth
                    @searchListSingleColumnWidth_DoubleColTest
                    @searchListDoubleColumnWidth_DoubleColTest
            */
            function getListCardColumnWidth() {
                if (window.innerWidth >= 1280) {
                    return 750;
                } else if (window.innerWidth >= 1007) {
                    return 375;
                } else {
                    return 0;
                }
            }

            var northLat = 33.902028;
            var southLat = 33.646176;
            var westLng = -84.671593;
            var eastLng = -84.289389;

            var Z_HEADER_HEIGHT = 80;
            var SRP_HEADER_HEIGHT = 55;

            // Only prefetch when the window is wide enough to display a map and list view
            if (window.innerWidth >= 1007){
                var boundsAndZoom = getBoundsAndZoomLevel(northLat, southLat, westLng, eastLng, window.innerHeight - SRP_HEADER_HEIGHT - Z_HEADER_HEIGHT, window.innerWidth - getListCardColumnWidth());
                window.boundsAndZoom = boundsAndZoom;
                // Use a placeholder image one zoom level out, since we are stretching the image out 2x, which has the effect of zooming in.
                window.selectedPrefetch = window.mapPlaceholders[boundsAndZoom.zoom-1];

                // Kick off a prefetch since the image won't be actually consumed till SSP initial render
                document.querySelector("#mapPrefetch").href = window.selectedPrefetch;
            }

if response.status_code == 200:
    # Parse the HTML content of the web page
    soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, "html.parser")

    # Find and print the relevant data

from bs4 import BeautifulSoup

# Send an HTTP GET request to the URL
url = "https://www.myfloridalicense.com/wl11.asp"
response = requests.get(url)

# Check if the request was successful
if response.status_code == 200:
    # Parse the HTML content of the page
    soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser')

    # Find the data you want to scrape (for example, scraping all links)
    links = soup.find_all('a')

    for link in links:
        print(link.get('href'))  # This will print the href attribute of each <a> element

    # You can adapt this code to scrape specific data you're interested in.

else:
    print("Failed to retrieve the web page. Status code:", response.status_code)

import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup

# Send an HTTP GET request to the URL
url = "https://www.myfloridalicense.com/wl11.asp"
response = requests.get(url)

# Check if the request was successful
if response.status_code == 200:
    # Parse the HTML content of the page
    soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser')

    # Find the data with proper headings and links
    data_with_headings = soup.find_all('td', style="height: 20px; background-color: #f7f7f7; font-size:14px; padding:7px 15px;")

    for item in data_with_headings:
        heading = item.find('a', class_='main')
        if heading:
            heading_text = heading.text
            link = item.find('a', href=True)
            if link:
                link_url = link['href']
                print(heading_text + " : " + link_url)

else:
    print("Failed to retrieve the web page. Status code:", response.status_code)

In [12]:
import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup

# Send an HTTP GET request to the URL
url = "https://www.myfloridalicense.com/wl11.asp"
response = requests.get(url)

# Check if the request was successful
if response.status_code == 200:
    # Parse the HTML content of the page
    soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser')

    # Find the link with the heading "Verify a Licensee"
    link = soup.find('a', text="Verify a Licensee")

    if link:
        link_url = link['href']
        print("Verify a Licensee Link:", link_url)
    else:
        print("Link not found")

else:
    print("Failed to retrieve the web page. Status code:", response.status_code)

key = 'hotels'
location = 'Texas City, TX'
url = 'https://www.yellowpages.com/search?search_terms={}&geo_location_terms={}%20City%2C%20TX&page='.format(key, location)
headers = {
    'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/118.0.0.0 Safari/537.36'
}
req = requests.get(url, headers=headers)

soup = BeautifulSoup(req.text, 'html.parser')
items = soup.findAll('div', 'v-card')

business_names = []  # Create a list to store business names

for item in items:
    name = item.find('a', 'business-name').text
    business_names.append(name)

# Print all the business names
for name in business_names:
    print(name)

import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup

key = 'hotels'
location = 'Texas City, TX'
url = 'https://www.yellowpages.com/search?search_terms={}&geo_location_terms={}%20City%2C%20TX&page='.format(key, location)
headers = {
    'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/118.0.0.0 Safari/537.36'
}
req = requests.get(url, headers=headers)

soup = BeautifulSoup(req.text, 'html.parser')
items = soup.findAll('div', 'v-card')

business_data = []  # Create a list to store business data (name and web link)

for item in items:
    name = item.find('a', 'business-name').text
    web_link = item.find('a', class_='track-visit-website')
    if web_link:
        web_link = web_link['href']
    else:
        web_link = "Web link not found"

    business_data.append((name, web_link))

# Print or process the business data (name and web link)
for name, web_link in business_data:
    print("Name:", name)
    print("Web Link:", web_link)
    print()

import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup

key = 'hotels'
location = 'Texas City, TX'
url = 'https://www.yellowpages.com/search?search_terms={}&geo_location_terms={}%20City%2C%20TX&page='.format(key, location)
headers = {
    'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/118.0.0.0 Safari/537.36'
}
req = requests.get(url, headers=headers)

soup = BeautifulSoup(req.text, 'html.parser')
items = soup.findAll('div', 'v-card')

business_data = []  # Create a list to store business data (name, web link, and phone)

for item in items:
    name = item.find('a', 'business-name').text
    web_link = item.find('a', class_='track-visit-website')
    if web_link:
        web_link = web_link['href']
    else:
        web_link = "Web link not found"
    phone = item.find('div', 'phones phone primary')
    if phone:
        phone = phone.text
    else:
        phone = "Phone not found"

    business_data.append((name, web_link, phone))

# Print or process the business data (name, web link, and phone)
for name, web_link, phone in business_data:
    print("Name:", name)
    print("Web Link:", web_link)
    print("Phone:", phone)
    print()

import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup

key = 'hotels'
location = 'Texas City, TX'

business_data = []  # Create a list to store business data (name, web link, and phone)

for page in range(1, 6):  # Assuming you want to scrape the first 5 pages
    url = 'https://www.yellowpages.com/search?search_terms={}&geo_location_terms={}%20City%2C%20TX&page={}'.format(key, location, page)
    headers = {
        'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/118.0.0.0 Safari/537.36'
    }
    req = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
    soup = BeautifulSoup(req.text, 'html.parser')
    items = soup.findAll('div', 'v-card')

    for item in items:
        name = item.find('a', 'business-name').text
        web_link = item.find('a', class_='track-visit-website')
        if web_link:
            web_link = web_link['href']
        else:
            web_link = "Web link not found"
        
        phone = item.find('div', 'phones phone primary')
        if phone:
            phone = phone.text
        else:
            phone = "Phone not found"

        business_data.append((name, web_link, phone))

# Print or process the business data (name, web link, and phone)
for name, web_link, phone in business_data:
    print("Name:", name)
    print("Web Link:", web_link)
    print("Phone:", phone)
    print()

import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import csv

key = 'hotels'
location = 'Texas City, TX'

business_data = []  # Create a list to store business data (name, web link, and phone)

for page in range(1, 6):  # Assuming you want to scrape the first 5 pages
    url = 'https://www.yellowpages.com/search?search_terms={}&geo_location_terms={}%20City%2C%20TX&page={}'.format(key, location, page)
    headers = {
        'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/118.0.0.0 Safari/537.36'
    }
    req = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
    soup = BeautifulSoup(req.text, 'html.parser')
    items = soup.findAll('div', 'v-card')

    for item in items:
        name = item.find('a', 'business-name').text
        web_link = item.find('a', class_='track-visit-website')
        if web_link:
            web_link = web_link['href']
        else:
            web_link = "Web link not found"
        
        phone = item.find('div', 'phones phone primary')
        if phone:
            phone = phone.text
        else:
            phone = "Phone not found"

        business_data.append((name, web_link, phone))

# Define the file path for the CSV file
file_path = r'C:\Users\Asrar\Downloads\business_data.csv'  # Use 'r' before the path to treat it as a raw string

# Save the business data as a CSV file
with open(file_path, 'w', newline='') as csv_file:
    writer = csv.writer(csv_file)
    writer.writerow(['Name', 'Web Link', 'Phone'])  # Write the header
    for data in business_data:
        writer.writerow(data)

print(f"Scraped data saved to {file_path}")

Scraped data saved to C:\Users\Asrar\Downloads\business_data.csv

import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import csv

key = 'hotels'
location = 'Texas City, TX'

business_data = []  # Create a list to store business data (name, web link, phone, and address)

for page in range(1, 6):  # Assuming you want to scrape the first 5 pages
    url = 'https://www.yellowpages.com/search?search_terms={}&geo_location_terms={}%20City%2C%20TX&page={}'.format(key, location, page)
    headers = {
        'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/118.0.0.0 Safari/537.36'
    }
    req = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
    soup = BeautifulSoup(req.text, 'html.parser')
    items = soup.findAll('div', 'v-card')

    for item in items:
        name = item.find('a', 'business-name').text
        web_link = item.find('a', class_='track-visit-website')
        if web_link:
            web_link = web_link['href']
        else:
            web_link = "Web link not found"
        
        phone = item.find('div', 'phones phone primary')
        if phone:
            phone = phone.text
        else:
            phone = "Phone not found"
        
        address = item.find('div', 'adr')
        if address:
            address = address.text
        else:
            address = "Address not found"

        business_data.append((name, web_link, phone, address))

# Define the file path for the CSV file
file_path =  r'C:\Users\Asrar\Downloads\business_data.csv' # Use 'r' before the path to treat it as a raw string

# Save the business data as a CSV file
with open(file_path, 'w', newline='') as csv_file:
    writer = csv.writer(csv_file)
    writer.writerow(['Name', 'Web Link', 'Phone', 'Address'])  # Write the header
    for data in business_data:
        writer.writerow(data)

print(f"Scraped data saved to {file_path}")

import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import csv

key = 'hotels'
location = 'Texas City, TX'

business_data = []  # Create a list to store business data (name and web link)

for page in range(1, 4):  # Assuming you want to scrape the first 5 pages
    url = 'https://www.yellowpages.com/search?search_terms={}&geo_location_terms={}%20City%2C%20TX&page={}'.format(key, location, page)
    headers = {
        'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/118.0.0.0 Safari/537.36'
    }
    req = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
    soup = BeautifulSoup(req.text, 'html.parser')
    items = soup.findAll('div', 'v-card')

    for item in items:
        name = item.find('a', 'business-name').text
        web_link = item.find('a', class_='track-visit-website')
        if web_link:
            web_link = web_link['href']
        else:
            web_link = "Web link not found"
        business_data.append((name, web_link))

# Save the data to a CSV file
with open('business_data.csv', mode='w', newline='') as file:
    writer = csv.writer(file)
    writer.writerow(["Name", "Web Link"])  # Write the header row
    for name, web_link in business_data:
        writer.writerow([name, web_link])
In [135]:
import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import csv

key = 'hotels'
location = 'Texas City, TX'

business_data = []  # Create a list to store business data (name and web link)

for page in range(1, 6):  # Assuming you want to scrape the first 5 pages
    url = 'https://www.yellowpages.com/search?search_terms={}&geo_location_terms={}%20City%2C%20TX&page={}'.format(key, location, page)
    headers = {
        'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/118.0.0.0 Safari/537.36'
    }
    req = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
    soup = BeautifulSoup(req.text, 'html.parser')
    items = soup.findAll('div', 'v-card')

    for item in items:
        name = item.find('a', 'business-name').text
        web_link = item.find('a', class_='track-visit-website')
        if web_link:
            web_link = web_link['href']
        else:
            web_link = "Web link not found"
        business_data.append([name, web_link])

# Save the data to a CSV file
with open('business_data.csv', mode='w', newline='', encoding='utf-8') as file:
    writer = csv.writer(file)
    writer.writerow(["Name", "Web Link"])  # Write the header row
    for data in business_data:
        writer.writerow(data)

import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import csv

key = 'hotels'
location = 'Texas City, TX'

business_data = []  # Create a list to store business data (name and web link)

for page in range(1, 3):  # Assuming you want to scrape the first 5 pages
    url = 'https://www.yellowpages.com/search?search_terms={}&geo_location_terms={}%20City%2C%20TX&page={}'.format(key, location, page)
    headers = {
        'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/118.0.0.0 Safari/537.36'
    }
    req = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
    soup = BeautifulSoup(req.text, 'html.parser')
    items = soup.findAll('div', 'v-card')

    for item in items:
        name = item.find('a', 'business-name').text
        web_link = item.find('a', class_='track-visit-website')
        if web_link:
            web_link = web_link['href']
        else:
            web_link = "Web link not found"
        business_data.append((name, web_link))

# Save business_data as a CSV file
with open('business_data.csv', 'w', newline='') as csvfile:
    csv_writer = csv.writer(csvfile)
    csv_writer.writerow(['Name', 'Web Link'])  # Write header
    csv_writer.writerows(business_data)  # Write data rows

print("business_data saved as business_data.csv")

business_data saved as business_data.csv

items = soup.findAll('div', 'listing-card')
for item in items:
    name = item.find('h1', class_='dockable business-name')
    if name:
        business_name = name.text.strip()
        print("Business Name:", business_name)
    else:
        print("Business Name not found for this listing")

# ... (your previous code)

for it in items:
    name = it.find('a', class_='business-name')
    if name:
        business_name = name.get_text(strip=True)
        print("Business Name:", business_name)
    else:
        print("Business Name not found")

    # Extract address
    address = it.find('div', class_='street-address')
    if address:
        business_address = address.get_text(strip=True)
        print("Address:", business_address)
    else:
        print("Address not found")

    # Extract website
    website = it.find('a', class_='track-visit-website')
    if website:
        business_website = website['href']
        print("Website:", business_website)
    else:
        print("Website not found")

    # Extract telephone
    phone = it.find('div', class_='phones phone primary')
    if phone:
        business_phone = phone.get_text(strip=True)
        print("Telephone:", business_phone)
    else:
        print("Telephone not found")
            # Extract image
    image = it.find('img', class_='lazy')
    if image:
        business_image = image['data-original']
        print("Image:", business_image)
    else:
        print("Image not found")
